The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Mary Kom and Sushil years best 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Mary Kom and Sushil years best 
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Mumbai: Cricket was pushed to the second rung as the Indian Davis Cup squad was declared the Team of the Year at the Sahara Indian Sports Awards here, on Saturday.         
	The top individual honours went to two Olympians, wrestler Sushil Kumar and pugilist MC Mary Kom who were conferred the Sportsman and Sportswoman of the Year awards.         
	While Kumar won Indias first ever World Championship gold in wrestling, in the 66kg freestyle category, Manipurs Mary Kom bagged her fifth consecutive world title in the 48kg category in Barbados earlier this year.         
	Sachin Tendulkar and Mithali Raj won the Cricketer of the Year in the mens and womens category respectively, while Grandmaster Viswanathan Anands victory over Veselin Topalov in the FIDE World Championship was declared as the Most Memorable Event of the Year.         
	Tendulkar also bagged the Sports Icon of the Millennium award.         
	Soumya Swaminathan, who won the World Junior (U-20) chess championship in Argentina, was conferred the Best Young Achiever award among women, while shooter Asher Noria received the award in the mens category for his double trap gold-winning performance at the Junior World Cup at Suhl, Germany.         
	The Coach of the Year was expectedly identified as Yashvir Singh who was instrumental in Sushil Kumars performance.         
	Sporting legends Gurbachan Singh Randhawa (athletics), Syed Hamid (football) and Manohar Topno (hockey) were honoured as the Unsung Heroes of yesteryears. Their prize included a cheque for Rs five lakh each.         
	Over 400 members of the Sports Journalists Federation of India (SJFI) participated in the nomination process. The winners were picked by a jury, headed by former Indian captain Sunil Gavaskar.         
	Other award winners         
	Outstanding Performance of the Year: Boxing  Suronjoy Singh; Table tennis  Achanta Sharath Kamal; Cue sports  Pankaj Advani; Athletics  Om Prakash Singh (shot put).         
	Outstanding Performance at Commonwealth Games: Gagan Narang and Deepika Kumari.                                                                                                                     
